<br>
We're also going to try something a little different this time.  The Oasis of Marr is a 15+ zone -- it's not the usual newbie zone.  But there's a real need for help there.  People get overpowered easily -- those crocodiles all look alike but they're not the same level!  <br>
<br>
Ghouls, madmen, and drybone skellies occasionally show up, making things VERY tough for people who are trying to run away from a bad pull.  People need heals, SoWs, and also -- unlike in newbie zones -- combat assistance.<br>
<br>
I do realize not everyone in the guild is 15+.  If there is a significant number of people who can't attend due to level, I will be happy to organize a party in the neighboring zone, the Northern Desert of Ro.  That's a lower level zone, and people need help there too, especially at the derv camps.<br>
<br>
I would like to have two Oasis groups -- one at the docks, and one at the second pillar.  The second pillar group should be at least level 20 due to dangers from wandering orcs and so forth.  The dock group can be 15+.  Higher level members will need to make sure the younger ones don't wander off or get isolated -- that way, you can take care of them if something appears out of nowhere.<br>
<br>
This will be a little more risky than some of our previous camps, but I think the reward will be in equal measure.  And anyway, nobody ever said helping others was easy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I hope to see you all there!  One more thing, this camp will be the last occasion (until August) at which new members can be tagged.  Please try to make it, so you can meet our new recruits and get to know them!<br>
<br>
