<br>
RLS &amp; GLS:<br>
1) Make sure you have some open inventory slots.  Find SYNTHAN in Gyspsy camp.  GIVE (not sell) her one at a time.<br>
You get: RLS (A research book) GLS:  A Concordance of Research (hold 6 items) You get: Gold (i think) and some nice exp.  <br>
2) Take the Concordance and Research books to any other gypsy* and sell them.  Depending on Charisma - CONCORDANCE=7-9 PLAT, Research book= a Handful of gold.<br>
<br>
Shaman need the Fish Scales for ENDURING BREATH* - and I guarantee that if you give a stack of the scales to any shaman, they will buff the bejabbers out of you.  If they don't..then spank them!<br>
<br>
Shokar has Hunting in High Keep - and doing no real damage with Velium Sword and Shield.  I NEEDED A TWO HAND SLASh, but my skill was only 31, and Goblins are not the critters to train on.  I left for Oasis at level 21...with my skill of 31 on two-hand slash.  I hunted CROCS.  DWATER , whatever was blue.  You can kill a Crocs momma right in front of him, and will not aggro it.  You can MED in their mouths, and they won't aggro...  No AGGRO=Safe Soloing.  <br>
The Crocs drop zero Loot...except for some words and runes..<br>
Now, I left at level 22 two - three days later, with a TWO-HAND SLASH of 98, a Fishing Skill of 56 (from about 20) I learned IKSAR and DWARVEN while partnering and about 100 PLAT**. <br>
<br>
Oh Yea - the Croc Exp is GREAT too.  Very fast leveling.<br>
<br>
So, in exchange of a dirt-poor mob, I increased my 2hs 67 Points, Fishing 34, learned two languages, and made a ton of plat from items brought with me.  I think that was a very Fair deal.  So, if anyone says to you OASIS ROTS...agree with them wholeheartedly!  Leaves more for you!<br>
<br>
ORC HIGHWAY = A Great spot to really get TEAM Exp.  Learn ASSIST, and how to help your casters stay alive.  This will be your first REAL threatening time working with Mezzers and dangerous multiple mobs.  The Drybones wander right into you.  In all, the Oasis of Marr is a GREAT GREAT Training area.  Sure other places have better loot, but this is the place to get ALL your melee skills up to CAPS.<br>
<br>
This is where Shokar stopped being a Liability, and became a Good MAIN tank or an EXCELLENT Backup tank.<br>
<br>
GIANTS:  People shout all over the zone for them, and once I found the spots to hunt from, never got bothered by them.<br>
THE PLATFORM:  I never hunted from there, as I wanted Crocs.  Thought the platform was in North Ro?  Not sure though.<br>
<br>
PULLSTEALING:  This is a good area to learn to run backwards.  So many people want crocs, that it is easy for your kill to be stolen.  Running backwards, people realize the kill is being pulled.  I always like to do a shout...<br>
/shout an OASIS reminder:  A Running CROC is probably being Pulled, check its health before you attack it...thank you!<br>
<br>
* Pulling from the Ocean:  Enduring Breath ON, swim around, and look for crocs there, they are plentiful underwater.  FUNNY MOMENT:  I was pulling from there, and my partner (an IKSAR) also dived in...I had NEVER seen an IKSAR underwater, and when I saw this HUGE ALIEN™ looking thing in the water, I almost spit my drink out...IKSARS look way scary underwater.<br>
** You see, I knew the loot was bad, so on the way, I took an hour and hunted WISPS, until I got nine GLS's.<br>
